# Refactor Plan – GB → GBC Evolution

## Phase 1 – Architecture Cleanup
Goal: Make GBC features pluggable without breaking DMG

### Actions
- Split emulator into subsystems:
  - cpu/
  - ppu/
  - mmu/
  - timer/
  - apu/
  - platform/ (ESP32-specific)
- Introduce `EmulatorMode { DMG, CGB }`
- All subsystems receive mode flag

## Phase 2 – Memory Refactor
Goal: Enable GBC banking cleanly

### Actions
- Replace single WRAM array with:
  - wram_bank0[4KB]
  - wram_banks[7][4KB]
- Replace VRAM with:
  - vram_banks[2][8KB]
- MMU routes reads/writes based on VBK / SVBK

## Phase 3 – PPU GBC Support
Goal: Color rendering without breaking DMG

### Actions
- Add BG/OBJ palette RAM:
  - BGPI/BGPD
  - OBPI/OBPD
- Decode tile attributes:
  - Palette number
  - VRAM bank
  - H/V flip
  - BG priority
- Maintain DMG fast-path rendering

## Phase 4 – Speed Switching
Goal: Support double-speed safely

### Actions
- Implement KEY1 register
- CPU cycles *= 2 in double-speed
- Timer and PPU adapt automatically
- STOP instruction triggers speed toggle

## Phase 5 – DMA / HDMA
Goal: Pokémon Crystal compatibility

### Actions
- Implement HDMA state machine
- HBlank DMA during mode 0
- CPU stalls during General DMA

## Phase 6 – Boot ROM
Goal: Accurate startup for all games

### Actions
- Add CGB boot ROM
- Auto-detect cartridge type
- Correct register initialization

## Phase 7 – Performance Pass (ESP32-S3)
Goal: 60 FPS stable

### Actions
- Mark hot functions IRAM_ATTR
- SPI DMA for ST7789
- Avoid per-pixel SPI writes
- Framebuffer double-buffering

## Phase 8 – Validation
Goal: Regression-free

### Actions
- Automated ROM test suite
- Save-state stress test
- Long Pokémon play session (10+ min)
